                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">I never understand why viruses are not life. Bacteria are life because they are essentially a single-cell organism and act like any cell in our body: they consume energy and produce waste. Viruses may not be a cell, but they can be damaged, they die, and they appear to be more than a simple chemical process.<span>
              </span><div class='reply'>        <p><font size="1">
